messages.text: I’m done playing games. I’m here for my daughter this time.
And to be a family again??
Whatever you want. I just want my daughter.
My daughter too. You forget that…
No tricks this time? No blood on the walls?
Your word has been a bit inconsistent lately.
I’d love to bicker, but I want my daughter.
I think you’ll like it here.
Wonderful view from our bedroom, overlooking the lake.
Can fish together, swim together, just be a family again.
Like I said. I just care about being with my daughter.
I just want you to love me.
You have to understand where I’m coming from...
I’m just a simple man who wants to be with his family.
You know, I should thank you.
Tell me where she is, Todd.
If you hadn’t left, I wouldn’t have realized how important you were to me.
I’m in the house just standing here...
We have a tracker on her?
The fuck? How far is that??
30 min. Out in the woods. Next to Lake Pete.
Get my units. Let's roll out.
Weird…my phone has never made that sound before...
I told you - we’re all here...
Is that a camera. In the corner there??
I don’t want anyone intruding on our space.
I AM upstairs. WHERE IS SHE?
Go down the hall and it's the room to your right.
She better be in one piece!
Have someone alert the authorities in Bryan.
We might need help. Not sure how much fire power this guy is packing.
Also, we ran the fingerprints on that finger.
It belongs to the neighbor that he killed. Daryl.
She’s a fighter. Like her mother.
Did you seriously think I was going to harm our daughter?
Oh god oh god oh god...
Not my fault. She wouldn’t eat.
But now we can be a happy family. All reunited.
Okay. I’m going to come down now.
Let’s advance. Don’t be afraid to shoot if engaged.
Explain to me why there are COPS outside?!
I'M GONNA KILL YOU FOR THIS!!!
You and that BITCH of a daughter!!
Interview transcribed by Bryan County Police Department.
Recorded after the events at 400 Barksdale Avenue.
Can you tell us what exactly happened?
I took Tasha, my daughter, and we fled downstairs.
He had a shotgun. He aimed it at us.
I threw Tasha behind a couch downstairs.
He fired, I dove, bullets hit my arm.
But I couldn’t feel them. Not then.
This was about the time the cops entered correct?
Right. They stormed in through the doors and windows.
Did you see them kill him?
No. I was with my daughter, holding her, behind the couch until it was over.
Then we were escorted out and taken to the hospital.
Can you tell us why you withheld information from the authorities?
You have to understand where I was coming from!
He said he was going to kill her if I came with them again!
Nothing. I just want to be with Tasha.
Of course. She is waiting outside.
